{"validation_override": true, "portal_release_date": "", "data_series_issue_identification_fra": "", "catalog_type": "Data | Donn\u00e9es", "title_fra": "Cartes et Plans du Canada", "keywords": "map, plan, chart, canada, history, cartography ", "data_series_issue_identification": "001028", "ready_to_publish": "", "digital_object_identifier": "", "subject": "History and Archaeology  Histoire et arch\u00e9ologie", "data_series_name_fra": "", "spatial_representation_type": "", "maintenance_and_update_frequency": "quarterly", "title": "Maps, Plans and Charts of Canada", "author_email": "open-ouvert@tbs-sct.gc.ca", "geographic_region": "", "notes_fra": "Depuis leur cr\u00e9ation en 1872, les Archives nationales du Canada, maintenant Biblioth\u00e8que et Archives Canada, acqui\u00e8rent, conservent et comm\u00e9morent le patrimoine cartographique du Canada. Aujourd'hui, ces fonds renferment plus de 2 millions de pi\u00e8ces. L'instrument de recherche suivant permet aux chercheurs de consulter environ 40 000 descriptions \u00e0 la pi\u00e8ce du \u00ab vieux catalogue sur fiches \u00bb. Ces documents sont d\u00e9crits dans la langue du cr\u00e9ateur; la plupart des descriptions n'existent qu'en anglais.", "id": "becd58f5-2751-4455-b3c2-21f5c3a923ae", "presentation_form": "", "spatial": "", "license_id": "", "resources": [{"url": "http://www.collectionscanada.gc.ca/obj/900/f11/001028_20100929.xml", "language": "English | Anglais", "resource_type": "Dataset", "format": "XML"}, {"url": "ftp://arcdm20.tor.ec.gc.ca/pub/dist/climate/CWEEDS_2005/ZIPPED%20FILES/ENGLISH/", "language": "French | Fran\\u00e7ais", "resource_type": "Dataset", "format": "XML"}], "browse_graphic_url": "", "topic_category": "", "endpoint_url_fra": "", "date_published": "2004-03-31", "time_period_coverage_start": "1872-01-01", "data_series_name": "", "url_fra": "", "endpoint_url": "", "time_period_coverage_end": "1872-01-01", "language": "", "date_modified": "2010-08-05", "url": "", "notes": "Since its inception in 1872, the National Archives of Canada, now Library and Archives Canada, has acquired, preserved and commemorated the cartographic heritage of Canada and there are now some two million items in the collection. This search tool provides access to approximately 40,000 item-level descriptions from the \"old map card catalogue.\" The item-level descriptions are written in the language of the original map, plan, or chart; the majority of the descriptions are written in English.", "owner_org": "75BDAB68-199F-4C06-92A3-E1E6769B0B8E", "keywords_fra": "carte, plan, charte, canada, histoire, cartographie", "resource_type": "file"}
{"validation_override": true, "portal_release_date": "", "data_series_issue_identification_fra": "", "catalog_type": "Data | Donn\u00e9es", "title_fra": "Fichiers m\u00e9t\u00e9orologiques canadiens pour calcul \u00e9nerg\u00e9tique (FMCCE)", "keywords": "temperature data ", "data_series_issue_identification": "", "ready_to_publish": "", "digital_object_identifier": "", "subject": "Economics and Industry  \u00c9conomie et industrie", "data_series_name_fra": "", "spatial_representation_type": "", "maintenance_and_update_frequency": "", "title": "Canadian Weather Year for Energy Calculation (CWEC)", "author_email": "open-ouvert@tbs-sct.gc.ca", "geographic_region": "", "notes_fra": "Ensembles de donn\u00e9es cr\u00e9\u00e9es en combinant 12 mois m\u00e9t\u00e9orologiques types choisis \u00e0 partir d'une base de donn\u00e9es couvrant habituellement 30 ans de donn\u00e9es des FMCEG. Les mois sont choisis par une comparaison statistique des moyennes mensuelles individuelles et des moyennes mensuelles \u00e0 long terme au regard du rayonnement global quotidien total, des temp\u00e9ratures du thermom\u00e8tre sec moyennes, minimales et maximales, des temp\u00e9ratures du point de ros\u00e9e moyennes, minimales et maximales ainsi que des vitesses du vent moyennes et maximales.\n", "id": "d2fab74f-3c92-4f76-8676-c26a95f6c3a1", "presentation_form": "", "spatial": "", "license_id": "", "resources": [], "browse_graphic_url": "", "topic_category": "", "endpoint_url_fra": "", "date_published": "2010-04-22", "time_period_coverage_start": "1953-01-01", "data_series_name": "", "url_fra": "http://www.climate.weatheroffice.gc.ca/Welcome_f.html?&", "endpoint_url": "", "time_period_coverage_end": "1953-01-01", "language": "", "date_modified": "", "url": "http://www.climate.weatheroffice.gc.ca/Welcome_e.html", "notes": "Datasets created by joining twelve Typical Meteorological Months selected from a database of, usually, 30 years of CWEEDS data. The months are chosen by statistically comparing individual monthly means with long term monthly means for daily total global radiation, mean, minimum and maximum dry bulb temperature, mean, minimum and maximum dew point temperature, and mean and maximum wind speed.\n", "owner_org": "49E2ADF4-AD7A-43EB-85C8-6433D37ED62C", "keywords_fra": "donn\u00e9es de temp\u00e9rature", "resource_type": "file"}
